article.headline: Appalachian St. 77, Elon 63
article.story: ELON, N.C. -- Kellen Brand scored 29 points to lead Appalachian State to a 77-63 victory over Elon on Saturday. Brand went 12 of 13 from the free-throw line and the Mountaineers (10-12, 7-7 Southern Conference) outrebounded the Phoenix (7-14, 4-9) 41-19 to sweep the season series. Brand, who missed his career high of 31 points set last month against Western Carolina, had 16 points in the first half as Appalachian State took a 39-29 lead. Elon cut the lead to 41-38 with 17:36 left in the game, but the Mountaineers went on an 11-2 run for a 52-40 lead with 11:47 remaining. A.J. Highsmith's 3-pointer gave the Mountaineers a 64-46 lead with 7:39 remaining. Josh Hunter had 12 points and 10 rebounds and Highsmith finished with 11 points for the Mountaineers. Josh Bonney scored 12 points and Devan Carter added 10 points for Elon.
